Here's the full setup:

**XAML — wrap CollectionView in RefreshView for pull-to-refresh:**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <VerticalStackLayout Grid.Column="1" VerticalOptions="Center">
                        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontAttributes="Bold" />
                        <Label Text="{Binding Description}" FontSize="12"
                               TextColor="{StaticResource Gray600}" />
                    </VerticalStackLayout>
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <Label Text="No items found."
                   HorizontalTextAlignment="Center"
                   VerticalOptions="Center" />
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel — using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm:**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    public ItemsViewModel(IApiService api, INavigationService nav)
    {
        _api = api;
        _nav = nav;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"detail?id={CurrentItem.Id}");

        // Clear selection so user can re-select the same item later
        CurrentItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
            {
                Items.Clear();
                foreach (var item in data)
                    Items.Add(item);
            });
        }
        finally
        {
            // Must set false to dismiss the refresh spinner
            IsRefreshing = false;
        }
    }
}
```

**Key bindings explained:**

| Property | Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` → `Items` | `ObservableCollection<T>` so UI auto-updates on add/remove |
| `SelectedItem` → `CurrentItem` | `TwoWay` so the VM receives the selected object |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` → `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on tap; navigates to detail page |
| `IsRefreshing` → `IsRefreshing` | `TwoWay` — set `false` when done to hide the spinner |
| `Command` → `RefreshCommand` | Triggers your API reload on pull-down |

**Important details:**
- Always use `ObservableCollection<T>`, not `List<T>` — swapping a list forces a full re-render.
- Set `CurrentItem = null` after navigation so the same item can be re-selected.
- Always set `IsRefreshing = false` in a `finally` block to guarantee the spinner dismisses.
- Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` to enable compiled bindings and catch errors at build time.
- Update collections on the UI thread via `MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`.
